What I don't understand is why it's more important to point out to the user that they are hitting race condition than fix what is actually causing it and let them continue what ever they were doing.

Lets say deleting the data from the backend store takes time, and you issue second delete, that will actually update the database and after that your subsequent requests instead of 204 will return correctly Invalid and tell you that the image is not stored in that store and those records will stay correct even if the original request did never finish due to the node crashing or what ever other reason.
